-----------------------------------------------------------------------
CAN A SINGLE CONSUMER CONSUME MULTIPLE PARTITIONS?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

YES.

A single Consumer can be assigned multiple Partitions.

Example:

Topic: Orders

Partitions:
    P0
    P1
    P2

Consumer Group: order-group

    Consumer-1
    Consumer-2

Kafka may assign Partitions like:

    P0 -> Consumer-1

    P1 -> Consumer-2

    P2 -> Consumer-1

Result:

    Consumer-1
        ├── P0
        └── P2

    Consumer-2
        └── P1

So Consumer-1 is consuming data from two different Partitions.

## IMPORTANT:
--------------

Within the same Consumer Group:

    One Partition can be assigned to only one Consumer at a time.

But:

    One Consumer can have multiple Partitions assigned to it.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
CAN A SINGLE CONSUMER CONSUME FROM MULTIPLE TOPICS?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

YES.

A Consumer can subscribe to multiple Topics and consume data from all
assigned Partitions across those Topics.

Example:

Topics:

    Orders
    Payments

Orders Topic Partitions:

    Orders-P0
    Orders-P1

Payments Topic Partitions:

    Payments-P0
    Payments-P1

Consumer:

    Consumer-1

Subscription:

    Consumer-1 subscribes to:

        Orders
        Payments

Kafka may assign:

    Orders-P0   -> Consumer-1
    Orders-P1   -> Consumer-1

    Payments-P0 -> Consumer-1
    Payments-P1 -> Consumer-1

Result:

    Consumer-1

        ├── Orders-P0
        ├── Orders-P1
        ├── Payments-P0
        └── Payments-P1

So a single Consumer can consume from:

    - Multiple Partitions of the same Topic
    - Multiple Partitions belonging to different Topics


## PARALLELISM NOTE
----------------------

Consumer continuously polls Kafka:

    consumer.poll(...)

A poll response may contain records from multiple assigned Partitions.

By default:

    1 Consumer = 1 Poll Thread

Therefore, a Consumer can read from multiple Partitions, but processing
may still happen sequentially.

If the application uses worker threads internally:

    Partition-0 -> Worker-1
    Partition-1 -> Worker-2
    Partition-2 -> Worker-3

then messages from different Partitions can be processed in parallel.

## IMPORTANT:
--------------

Kafka allows a Consumer to read from multiple Partitions, but true
parallel processing depends on the application's implementation.


