Offset 2 -> C
Offset 3 -> D

Kuch delete nahi hua.

Fir Delete Kab Hota Hai?

Retention policy decide karti hai.

Kafka bolta hai:

Main data ko kitne time tak rakhunga before deleting? (Time based retention)

Ya

Main kitna storage limit tak data rakhunga before deleting? (Size Based Retention)

---------------------------------
KAFKA ME RETENTION SETTINGS:
----------------------------------

1. Broker Level (Global Default)
2. Topic Level (Override)


1: BROKER LEVEL RETENTION (Global Default)
--------------------------------------------

Agar kisi topic ne apni retention define nahi ki, to ye broker level retention use hogi. i.e Broker-level retention acts as the default for all topics
Note : Retention policy topic ke saare partitions par apply hoti hai, na ki kisi individual/particular partition par.

Kafka broker configuration me define kar sakte ho:

# Time based retention
  log.retention.hours=170

ya

# Size based retention
  log.retention.ms=604800000


## DEFAULT BROKER LEVEL RETENTION 
----------------------------------

Default Time-Based Retention:
log.retention.hours=168 (Matlab 7 days) 


Default size-Based Retention:
log.retention.bytes=-1 (Matlab: No size limit)

Size ki wajah se deletion nahi hogi.

Deletion sirf time-based retention ke basis par hogi.

Aur tumne: Topic level retention nahi di and Broker level retention bhi explicitily nahi di to Kafka broker ye default values use karta hai. 


## TRULY INFINITE RETENTION:
-----------------------------

Agar theoretically indefinitely retain karna ho to:

log.retention.ms=-1
log.retention.bytes=-1

Dono disable karne padenge.

Lekin production me almost kabhi nahi karte, warna disk bhar jayegi.


2: TOPIC LEVEL RETENTION (Most Common in Production)
--------------------------------------------------------

Topic-level configuration broker-level retention ko override kar deti hai.

Yaani agar tumne kisi specific topic par retention define ki hai, to us topic ke liye broker ki default retention settings use nahi hongi.

Suppose orders topic me sirf 1 partition hai.

Kafka internally partition ko multiple log segments me divide karke store karta hai.

Partition-0

Segment-1

Offset 0 -> A
Offset 1 -> B
Offset 2 -> C

Segment-2

Offset 3 -> D
Offset 4 -> E
Offset 5 -> F

Segment-3

Offset 6 -> G
Offset 7 -> H
Offset 8 -> I


1: TIME BASED RETENTION:
---------------------------

Example:

@Bean
public NewTopic ordersTopic() {

    return TopicBuilder.name("orders")
            .partitions(3)
            .replicas(3)
            .config(
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_CONFIG,
                TopicConfig.CLEANUP_POLICY_DELETE
            )
            .config(
                TopicConfig.RETENTION_MS_CONFIG,
                String.valueOf(7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) // 7 days
            )
            .build();
}

