14. LOG COMPACTION
===============================================================================

Retention ka Goal:
-> Storage bachana
-> Purana data delete karna

Compaction ka Goal:
-> Har key ki latest value bacha ke rakhna
-> Purani history corresponding to us key delete ho sakti hai


Log Compaction sirf tab useful hai jab messages ke paas KEY ho. Producer jab message publish karta hai to optionally ek KEY bhi pass kar sakta hai.

Ye KEY do kaam karti hai:

1. Partition decide karne me help karti hai
   partition = hash(key) % number_of_partitions

2. Compaction ke time Kafka isi KEY ka use karta hai ye identify karne ke liye
   ki kaunse records same entity ko represent karte hain.


ONE-LINE DEFINITION :
Log Compaction is a Kafka cleanup strategy that retains the latest record
for each key while allowing older records with the same key to be removed.


